Singapore shares may move higher as funds return . Singapore shares may move a little higher on Tuesday in anticipation of better fund buying following public holidays in Britain and the United States , dealers said . Both major markets were closed on Monday , leaving institutional activity minimal . On Monday , the Straits Times Industrials Index ( STII ) marked time , ending 0 . 96 points higher at 2 , 056 . 32 with a modest 131 . 4 million shares traded . But dealers said the tone of the market had been mildly supportive thanks to Wall Street ' s recent upward momentum . The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 87 . 78 points to close at 7 , 345 . 91 last Friday , a record high . - - Singapore newsroom ( 65 8703199 ) 
